Black, Indian and coloured medical practitioners marched on Discovery Health to raise their concerns. JOHANNESBURG - Medical aids must end racial discrimination against healthcare professionals. That's the demand from a group of private doctors who claim they're being treated unfairly. Black, Indian and coloured medical practitioners marched on Discovery Health to raise their concerns. READ: Medical aids accused of racist mistreatment But the company insists it's against any discrimination against healthcare professionals. t maintains any action it takes against doctors is based on tips-offs from the public or statistical analysis.
Discovery says it will respond to the doctors' grievances within the seven days it's been given.